      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "On suppose $a_{12} \\ne 0$, et on décompose $A$ sous la forme :\n    $A = \\begin{pmatrix} J &U \\cr {-{}^tU} &V\\cr\\end{pmatrix}$\n    avec $J = \\begin{pmatrix} 0 &a_{12} \\cr -a_{12} &0 \\cr\\end{pmatrix}$.\\par\n    Soit $P = \\begin{pmatrix} I_2 &-J^{-1}U \\cr 0 &I_{n-2}\\cr\\end{pmatrix}$.\n   \\begin{enumerate}",
        "html": ""
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "c458278d-ffb6-4d21-b327-b514717a0c38",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que $P$ existe et est inversible.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que <span class=\"math inline\">\\(P\\)</span> existe et est inversible.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "3e0e206d-49bf-4d60-ae78-3f1d58a75d78",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Calculer $AP$.",
        "html": "<p>Calculer <span class=\"math inline\">\\(AP\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "7656342d-4011-4c4c-a693-fb093cd188cd",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "En déduire que $\\mathrm{rg}(A) = 2 + \\mathrm{rg}({}^tUJ^{-1}U + V)$.",
